definition:
A man of the Arabs living at the time of the Patriarchs, first mentioned at Gen.25.15; 
 son of: Ishmael (H3458); 
 brother of: Nebaioth (H5032), Kedar (H6938), Adbeel (H0110), Mibsam (H4017), Mishma (H4927), Dumah (H1746), Massa (H4854), Hadad (H2301), Tema (H8485), Jetur (H3195), Naphish (H5305) and Mahalath (H4258); also called Nodab at 1Ch.5.19; 
Also named: no.dav (נוֹדָ֑ב "Nodab" H5114) 
 § Kedemah = "original"
 the youngest son of Ishmael
